channel.title: uTorrent Problems?
channel.description:
[URL=http://img16.imageshack.us/i/utorrentx.jpg/][IMG]http://img16.imageshack.us/img16/9348/utorrentx.jpg[/img][/URL] [URL=http://g.imageshack.us/img16/utorrentx.jpg/1/][IMG]http://img16.imageshack.us/img16/utorrentx.jpg/1/w640.png[/img][/URL]
After I "run.bat" and turn on my No-Ip, I turn on uTorrent and this is what pops up.
I'm not sure what I'm supposed to see so I'm not sure if this is good or not.
If anyone knows what's going on, help would be appreciated. :)
*EDIT*~~ After I do all of this I go to: http://www.google.ca/search?hl=en&ei=TAB4SticE9SJtgf0w_HMAQ&sa=X&oi=spell&resnum=0&ct=result&cd=1&q=runescape+status+checker&spell=1 , after you click the link, 2 down there should be a google. I go into that, type my Server name where it's required and it tells me that my server is still offline. ~~*EDIT*
Thanks, Aleksander.

item.title: uTorrent Problems?
item.dc:creator: @i_weed_i1 i weed i_
item.description:
@i_weed_i1 wrote:

It’s suppose to pop up, utorrent isn’t just for private servers. It’s used to download torrents. If that happens again just click the x button, It should still be running on lower right hand corner.

Read full topic
